args:
The prince and his companions stop in at
a lovely snowy town famed for its children's
choir. The group opts to have a peek at their
recital, but the show is interrupted by a fiend
attack. The prince and his friends then engage
in battle in order to keep everyone safe.
Roast 'em and toast 'em aaaand...boom!\nThat oughta put a bow on this little fiend-\nslayin' commission.
I know we had to pursue those fiends,\nbut I'm still surprised at how far afield\nwe've traveled.
Seriously, it's colder than a well-digger's\nlunchpail up in this joint!
R-right?! Let's find a town to warm up in\nbefore we make our way back home.
There's actually one near here.\nWhat say we drop by?
Ah, I know that oneâ€”and given the\nseason, this might be the perfect time\nfor us to pay it a visit.
Eh, you'll see when we get there.\nC'mon, future icicles! I'll lead the way.
Who would have thought there'd be a\ntown nestled between these mountains?\nAnd it's so well-guarded, to boot!
I'm still curious what we're here for.
That's because this is the hometown of\nthe Harmonia Choir.
It's a famous choir that only the most\nskilled young singers can hope to join.
They sing with pure soprano voices, and\ntheir songs are said to ward off calamity.
And once a year around this time,\nthey throw a huge song party!
It's called a ï¼‚recital,ï¼‚ ya doof! Not a\nï¼‚song party.ï¼‚ I just hope we're in time\nto catch it.
AAAUGH! A polar bear!\n...Wait, no. It's just a fiend.\n...AAAUGH! A fieeeeend!
Good heavens! First I'm a polar bear,\nthen a fiend? How rude!
I am the dragon Maritimus, and I am\npleased to make your acquaintance.
But you can call me Mariti if you want to\nthrow a little extra cute into it.
It's nice to meet you, Mariti.
You seem pretty used to people, for a\ndragon. What are you doing here in the\nmiddle of a town like this?
Ah, that! I'm here because I'm the owner\nof the Harmonia Choir.
Wait, sorry. Time out.\nA DRAGON owns a choir?
Er, yes? I've always watched over them,\nactually.
And it was worth it, because now we get\nvisitors coming from all around to hear us!
That's why you're all here, yes?
Of COURSE it is! Now comeâ€”I'll show you\nthe way to the recital hall.
Wait, the recital is TODAY?! How lucky!
All right, team, let's follow Mariti.
And now, ladies and gentlemen, I give to\nyou...the recital hall! Yaaaay, recital hall!\nRight this way, please.
Holy snotballs, look at all the peeps!\nYou weren't kidding about this being\na hot ticket.
Heh. Indeed. Of course, it helps that this\nyear's recital is a teensy bit special.
Ahem! Well, in celebration of the 100th\nanniversary of the recital, two of our\nformer members have come to join us.
The first is the conductor, Vixel,\nwho will be lifting his baton for\nall of you tonight.
Exciting, no? Behold the man himself!
Hello, distinguished guests. I humbly\nwelcome you to the Harmonia Choir's\nannual recital.
I am Vixel, a graduate of the Harmonia\nChoir. I will have the honor of being your\nconductor today.
All of us will do our utmost to ensure each\nand every one of you enjoys the singing on\nthis most festive occasion.
A professional conductor? Interesting.\nThat's not something you see every day.
But of course, it's not just tonight's\nhonored guests who are amazing.
Our entire choir is made up of incredibly\nhard-working young vocalists who are\nabsolutely BURSTING with talent.
And among their number is the particularly\nexceptional young Elias!

His voice is said to bring tears to even
the most hardened curmudgeon, which
is why we've given him the featured
solo in tonight's performance.
Oh man, now I REALLY wanna hear this\ncrazychoir do its thing!
Ah, but do you remember when I said we\nhad one more special guest?
At the risk of sounding like an elitist snob,\nshe is freakin' AMAZING.
Ding ding ding! You nailed it! Our second\nspecial recital guest is none other than\nthe famed songstress herself!

Famous ain't even the half of it. Even I'VE
heard of her, and all I know about music
is that ya strum a guitar to make a buncha
pretty noises come out.
I can't believe I'm going to be able to\nhear her perform...
And now, ladies and gentlemen, let me\npresent tonight's main event! Put your\nhands together for the Harmonia Choâ€”
Oh my stars and garters! FIENDS!
Oh dear! I thought security in this town\nwould be impenetrable.
Maritimus, take the audience and the choir\nmembers and get them to safety.
We'll take care of things here. Now hurry!
Don't worry about usâ€”we know how to\nuse the business end of a sword.
Guys, don't wanna worry nobody, but we\ngot fiends floodin' into town.
Then we'll just have to force them back\nout. Come on, everyone!
